A vintage 1970s computer terminal aesthetic showing a glowing green phosphor CRT monitor displaying cascading lines of shell script code, surrounded by warm amber desk lamp lighting casting dramatic shadows across a weathered wooden desk cluttered with handwritten notes on yellowed paper, coffee-stained technical manuals, and a chunky mechanical keyboard with worn keycaps, the scene bathed in nostalgic sepia tones with film grain texture and slight vignetting around the edges, capturing the romance and craftsmanship of old-school computing culture.
